title: Quality Assurance Analyst
description: Millennium Systems International is an exciting and dynamic software company based in Parsippany, New Jersey. The company has built a reputation for producing high quality, award winning applications for the Beauty & Clinic Industries since 1987. It’s commitment to delivering excellent customer service has contributed to its ongoing success. We are in search of a Quality Assurance Analyst whom will help supplement the growth & scaling of the company. We are looking for a highly motivated, results driven technology individual, who has strong technical skills. Looking for creative and talented Computer Science graduate with 1-2 years’ experience. Able to perform software testing including designing and execution of test cases. Perform software feature analysis, test cases analysis, user stories analysis, software review and defect tracking system.
skills: SQL, Database, API, web/mobile apps, organized, coding languages

title: Jr. Big Data Engineer
description: You will be joining our growing team of analytics experts. We want individuals who are comfortable asking “why”. The ideal candidate is a data pipeline builder and data wrangler who enjoys optimizing data systems and building them from the ground up. The right candidate will be excited by the prospect of optimizing or even re-designing a company’s data architecture to support next generation and data initiatives. They must be self-directed and comfortable supporting the data needs of multiple teams, systems and products. They are a team player possessing strong analytical as well as technical skills and are able to communicate the logic behind technical decisions to non-tech stakeholders.
skills: SQL, Relational databases, Management, Interpersonal skills, Big data, Data structures, metadata, workload management

title: Human Resources Generalist
description: In this role you will be a human resource professional at the organization and part of a team of ten. You will be responsible for compensation strategy, employee benefits administration and talent development and engagement, employee communications, performance management culture and wellness programs, employee relations
skills: Verbal skills, communication skills, conflict resolution, problem-solving, Microsoft office suit, HRIS, talent management systems

title: Real Estate Agent - Training Provided

There’s a reason that we’ve passed every other real estate company, and we’re now the largest (and still fastest growing) real estate company in North America with over 175,000 associates.
